org.jamesframework.core.search.neigh.subset

Class SwapMove

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jamesframework.core.search.neigh.subset.SwapMove
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Move<SubsetSolution>, SubsetMove

    public class SwapMove
extends Object
implements SubsetMove
    Simple subset move that removes a single ID from the current selection and replaces it with a new ID which was previously not selected.
    Author:
    Herman De Beukelaer

      • SwapMove

        public SwapMove(int add,
        int delete)
        Creates a new swap move with specified IDs to add to and remove from the current selection when being applied to a given subset solution. Both IDs can not be equal.
        Parameters:
        add - ID to add
        delete - ID to delete
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if add == delete

    • Method Detail

      • apply

        public void apply(SubsetSolution solution)
        Apply this swap move to a given subset solution. The move can only be applied to a solution for which the added ID is currently not selected and the deleted ID is currently selected. This guarantees that calling undo(SubsetSolution) will correctly undo the move.
        Specified by:
        apply in interface Move<SubsetSolution>
        Parameters:
        solution - solution to which to move will be applied
        Throws:
        SolutionModificationException - if the added ID is already selected, the deleted ID is already unselected, or any of both IDs does not correspond to an underlying entity

      • undo

        public void undo(SubsetSolution solution)
        Undo this swap move after it has been successfully applied to the given subset solution, by removing the newly added ID and re-adding the deleted ID.
        Specified by:
        undo in interface Move<SubsetSolution>
        Parameters:
        solution - solution to which the move has been applied
